<a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/news_page.php?archive=true&step=25&menustr=060000000000">&gt;next articles</a><br /><span class="headers">July 12, 2003 - Gibber times 10!!</span>
<p>
It seems I was premature in promising that the next update would be from the new site. There was just a loud BANG from downstairs ... the House Ogre's computer literally blew up ... it'll be a few days before the replacement power supply is here. <i>(And we mean literally blew up!! I almost fell out of my chair in startlement. - Ngreth)</i> You guessed it ... there's irreplaceable info on that machine that we need in order to move the DB from the test site to the production side. We'll give a new ETA when able.</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">July 12, 2003 - {Gibbers}</span>
<p>
I am beyond swamped right now. I'm not even sure I am coherent. But I need to give you folks some updates, so bear with me, please. 

The next update you see, Bristlebane willing, will be from the new database-driven site. Yes, there will still be extra features added, and things changed once we launch. Patience, grasshoppers! :) 

While the multi-yield mana vial spells and the like are quite happy (spell vendor in the EC tunnel), the <b>multi-yield cultural metal enchants are not working as intended</b>. This is acknowledged as a known bug, and will be fixed with the next patch. (Currently requires 5 metal, returns only 1). 

As an FYI, the basic mana vial spells are now sold in High Keep as well as in the brownie village in Lesser Faydark - this should save some creative contortions when shopping for these spells. 

For those who have been flooding me with private messages of concern, yes I am alive, no you have NOT seen me much, if at all, in game. Currently, the game is just too much like work, partly due to the demands of the site and the database, partly due to the demands of too many folks who want to make small-talk within 30 seconds of me logging on. I need a break. Badly. Just leave me be to destress, please. I'll still be in when the devs ask me to test something, but other than that, don't expect to see me for a bit -- even on my bazaar mule, since several folks have taken to tell-spamming him demanding that I come play, etc., etc. It's just too much hassle and very unfun for me. </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">June 13, 2003 - Beta!</span>
<p>
The <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?p=62364#62364">cat saga</a> is finally done, and I'm pleased to announce the beta launch of our database. Over the next couple of hours, I'll be wandering through the various forums, doing last-minute trivial updates to the main site, then dropping sticky topics into each appropriate forum for folks to post new trivial and stat updates. Posts will stay in that thread for the next month and NOT be updated on the main site, as I want the site to be stable while testers are cross-referencing what's on the current site with what's in the database. Updates will go into the database, of course, but folks are going to have to rely more heavily on the message boards until the database is launched to the public in a month or so.
<p>As we start this final phase, let me do something that hearkens back to my days as a Project Manager ... "managing expectations."
<p>When the database finally goes live, you WILL see:
            <ul>
              <li>Over 6000 tradeskill recipes -- all general tradeskill recipes currently known, as well as some of the quest recipes</li>
     <li>Over 8000 items -- everything that we know is used in or produced by tradeskills</li>
              <li>Over 2500 mobs -- including all known tradeskill vendors and mobs with tradeskill drops</li>
              <li>Around 2000 sources -- tying the mobs, plus fish and forages to the appropriate items that they supply.</li>
              <li>Varying ways to search the above for recipes, sources, and more</li>
              <li><i>Hopefully</i> speedier updates to the site, as it takes less time and effort to make updates to the site and it is easier for us to set up limited access rights to volunteer editors.</li>
</ul>
<p>What you will NOT see:
            <ul>
              <li>Those rassenfrassen 
                advertisements that seem to be on almost every site you hit these 
                days.</li>
              <li>The even 
                more annoying (in my book) messages that say you must be a paying 
                member to access certain content.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We continue to fund the site out of our own pockets, assisted by <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g206">generous donations from the community</a>. Fates willing, we can continue to work this way without it becoming too draining on our resources, though we'll definitely never make it rich off the site! ;) Here's to a successful beta!  I truly hope you'll all be pleasantly impressed with the results of all this hard work, muss and fuss.
            <p></p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-14 08:32:38&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">June 11, 2003 - Wheeeee!</span>
<p>
<p>Today's front 
              page update will hopefully make up for the fact that there's not 
              been a front page update in almost a month.</font>
            <p>The patch has 
              several items of interest to tradeskillers. Below are some of the 
              highlights (discussion and details <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=8427">can 
              be found on the boards</a>):</font>
            <ul>
              <li>They stack?! 
                Valor crystals, ceramic lining, holgresh fur, casks. All of these 
                may seem like minor things to non-tradeskillers, but there's a 
                lot of rejoicing around here.</li>
              <li>Shared bank 
                space! Two more bank slots have been made available that are shared 
                across all characters on an account. (No no drop or no rent items, 
                and watch those lore tags!) This will be a boon for those who 
                need to mule tradeskill supplies around on a single account.</li>
              <li>The Kunark 
                catfish croak sandwich quest is finally in working order. The 
                reclusive sewer catfish are back in the waters of East and West 
                Cabilis, and that ever-hungry Klok Foob will happily accept donations 
                of two of his munch break favorites, those yummy catfish croak 
                sandwiches. Once the servers are stabilized today, hopefully someone 
                can provide us with information on the completion of this quest.</li>
              <li>Veksar. 
                A new zone! So far, there's only a few forages, that are shared 
                with other zones, and no zone specific fish, but one never knows 
                what else might be in there.</li>
              <li>Tradeskill 
                item tag. This one is viewed with mixed reactions around here, 
                and may still need a few kinks ironed out. For now, our database 
                will NOT be tracking this new flag, as it would delay our launch 
                by quite a bit.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>What's this 
              about the database?! Only a true follower of Bristlebane would be 
              excited about announcing a database beta launch for a Friday the 
              13th ... I don't know where that leaves me, as I'm alternately excited, 
              and stressed to the tips of my toes about this one. We'll have more 
              information about this later, and there will be a post on the message 
              boards in the DenMother's Corner if we find a need for more testers. 
              For now, the important information is: beta starting Friday, full 
              launch of this in a month or so if all goes well, and site updates 
              will be "locked" once Friday hits. (Once we're in beta, 
              we'll have special sticky threads to track new trivials and stats 
              and such, but we're going to stop with this time-consuming double 
              and triple-editing of information and focus all our energy on getting 
              the database updated.)
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">May 14, 2003 - Patch Day</span>
<p>
<p>Today's patch contains a few items of interest to tradeskillers. My comments follow the patch items in bold italics:
            <ul>
              <li> <strong>GM Baking Spoon</strong> - On Firiona Vie, the Grandmaster's 
                Baking Spoon was not no-drop. This allowed players to give out 
                an unlimited number of 100% weight reduction bags. This obviously 
                was not the intention for that item, so we have made the Grandmaster's 
                Baking Spoon no drop on Firiona Vie. -<em> <strong>erm ... whoops?</strong></em></li>
              <li> <strong>NPCs returning bags empty</strong> - NPCs that return 
                items that they do not need were returning all containers empty, 
                regardless of what was inside the container. NPCs that refuse 
                unusable items will now also return bags with their contents intact. 
                - <em><strong>some of us tend to get ahead of ourselves when questing, 
                and hand the wrong item in to an NPC, or forget to hit the combine 
                button on the container before giving it to the quest NPC. This 
                should save us from some lost items</strong>.</em></li>
              <li><strong> NPCs returning multiple items</strong> - If a character 
                gave an NPC multiples of the same item, the NPC would only give 
                back one of them if he did not want them. We have fixed this so 
                that now those items will be returned. Such items will be stacked 
                on your cursor. Just click the item that is on your cursor into 
                your inventory and the next one will appear on your cursor. Keep 
                clicking them into your inventory until you have them all back. 
                BE WARNED that any of these items that you have not returned to 
                your inventory will be lost if you zone or go linkdead before 
                you get them back into your inventory. <em>- t<strong>his goes 
                hand-in-hand with the line item above it. Sometimes we're in such 
                a hurry to finish a frustrating tradeskill quest that we don't 
                pay as much attention to this as we should. Re-read this one carefully 
                to be sure you know how to get those multiple items back into 
                your inventory!</strong></em></li>
              <li><strong>Giant Yellow Jackets</strong> - The chance to find a 
                thorax on the corpses of these creatures seemed too low, so we 
                have increased it. - <em><strong>used in newbie armor quests, 
                this should lessen the frustration of those trying for this item</strong></em></li>
              <li> <strong>Added Honey Mush Bread to Cabilis Vendors</strong> 
                - This is an item needed for a quest that was unavailable. - <em><strong>We've 
                been trying for years to figure out this recipe! It's lovely to 
                hear that some lucky vendor has found a source for this bread. 
                <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=q21&menustr=120030000000">The quest writeup</a> will be 
                updated as details become available.</strong></em></li>
              <li><strong> Combining Stacks of items</strong> - Attempting to 
                combine stacked items in a container will no longer work. The 
                items must be separated first. This change will prevent items 
                from being lost due to accidentally combining with them stacked. 
                A dialogue will pop up, warning the player to separate the objects. 
                -<em><strong> a partial fix for this went in a while back for 
                some tradeskill containers. This seems to be a continuation of 
                that fix. As usual, report on the boards if you find something 
                still accepting stacks of items in a tradeskill combine.</strong></em><br>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>Work on the database continues, thanks in no small part to the 
              database volunteers who have put large chunks of their time and 
              energy into the project. We're still not ready to give an ETA, as 
              the more we get done, the more we find needs to be done, but we 
              are making good progress.</p>
            </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-12 02:43:38&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">May 01, 2003 - At Long Last!</span>
<p>
<p>There are two items in the "at last" category today. Depending on what your tradeskill focus is, one, or both, may be of interest to you.
<p>Some of the "old cultural" armor sets that had the same name for more than one collection of normal vs imbued/enchanted vs enchanted set have had unannounced name changes. It will take a bit before we'vegot the site (and the database) updated accordingly, but we're <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=7150">gathering information here</a> on the new names. Note that sets that have multiple flavors of deity-specific imbues, such as imbued field plate and imbued steelsilk were <i>NOT</i> included in this name change.
<p>I'm sure the skeptics among you had long given up on this following annoucement, but we're finally ready to announce that our database is ready for alpha testing. (Sometimes, even <em>*I*</em> wasn't sure we'd ever hit this point, as it has been a very overwhelming task, and real life has thrown us many curve balls since we started this project.) We are NOT looking for added volunteers at the moment, so please, don't join the folks who have already swamped me with private messages containing well-meaning offers of help. I've given up even attempting to respond to them all at this point, as they're eating up far too much time that I <i>need</i> to be spending on the current site and on the database. When we are ready to announce beta (we have no ETA), we will either have a post asking for volunteers, or we will be contacting folks directly. 
<p>I can't stress this enough. Don't swamp us with tells. Don't send us private messages offering to help. Don't make unsolicited posts offering to help. Please, such "help" will only add to our workload instead of helping us. <i>(And it's very likely that we'll totally ignore you and that folks on the message boards will start quoting this front page update at you, since we want folks helping us that are willing and able to follow instructions, and if you're bugging us after seeing this post, you're NOT going to be someone we'll choose to help relieve our workload, hm?)</i>
<p>I truly don't want to seem ungrateful, as without all you wonderful folks that have volunteered information and encouragement over the years, not to mention the dedicated moderators and database volunteers who have kept me from going totally insane, but I'm a very overwhelmed redhead right now, and until this thing is fully launched, I'm fighting a very strong urge to hide in some deep dark corner and tell the world to go away. Of course, if I did that, I'd never get the durn thing launched, <i>despite</i> all the hard work done by my husband and others to get all the technical requirements and searches sorted out.            </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-05-01 06:06:00&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">April 22, 2003 - Quest Update</span>
<p>
Thanks to some added quest text from VI, at long last the Planes of Power <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=q57&menustr=120055000000">Aid Grimel quest</a> has been completely solved. The quest writeup has been updated, and the party platter recipe has also been added to the database and to the <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=149&rsa=Baking&sub=pop&sb=item&menustr=080020060000">PoP Baking Recipes page</a>. My thanks to all who aided in deciphering this quest, and to Kronepsis in particular for maintaining an up-to-date quest summary that I could put on the site.
<p>There is some <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=6360">weirdness going on with DNCs and disconnects</a> lately, especially in high-lag  areas such as the bazaar. The folks at VI are aware of the problem, and are working on resolving it. In the meantime, I'd recommend doing any important combines in quieter zones, and to do a quick camp and return after your most important skillups/successful combines so that you don't lose anything vital.            </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-12 02:46:46&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">April 08, 2003 - Patch Day</span>
<p>
<p>I'm slowly recovering from the Fan Faire and a week-long visit from my in-laws that started almost as soon as I returned from Vegas and am trying to catch up on both my sleep and site updates. as long as I don't try to do updates in my sleep, we should be all set. ;)
<p>Today's patch has a few items of specific interest to tradeskillers. In the "small but still important" category is the fact that saltwater seaweed, used for a human <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=37&rsa=Brewing&sb=item&sub=tempers-tannins&menustr=080030030000">smithing temper</a>, is finally stackable. This won't affect a ton of folks, but it's still very good news. Of more major note is the fact that how illusions affect faction has changed, and it has caused some unexpected problems when <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=45">obtaining the enchanter mana vial series of spells</a>. The powers that be have been alerted as to the specific issues with obtaining those spells, and will be looking into it. For now, your best bet if you need to acquire the spells is to use druid/ranger wolf form (enchanter illusion spirit wolf will NOT work).
            </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-12 02:55:37&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">April 08, 2003 - ... One More Thing!</span>
<p>
<p>If you are one of the many folks confuzzled about which of the new spell research drops should be saved for whom, you may want to keep the listing of drops for <a href="http://eqtraders.com/sources/source_trade_page.php?st=Spell%20Research&menustr=110120000000">LoY spell research</a> near at hand. (A huge thanks go out to Verdandi for whipping this new section into shape so quickly!!)
<p><strong>Addendum:</strong> All right, so I was wrong. It wasn't just "one" more thing today, but two. I'd like to add a quick reminder that pre-registration for the Fan Faire in Las Vegas ends on Monday, March 10th. After that time, you'll have to pay the higher rate of $100. Attendees  must book their own travel and hotel reservations. SOE has made arrangements for EverQuest Fan Faire attendees with the Las Vegas Hilton, Alexis Park Hotel, Embassy Suites Convention Center, and Southwest Airlines for special rates. For more information, please visit the <a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/fanfaire/index.jsp" target="_new">official EverQuest Fan Faire website</a>. Hope to see some of you there! </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

