		Last Modified on: 2003-06-12 03:02:48&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">March 05, 2003 - Odds and Ends</span>
<p>
<p>For those of you, like me, that seem to be perpetually lost, the new LoY map feature is a godsend. However, if you're like me, pretty much all you were seeing were blank maps at first, even for zones folks were saying "look at the map!" Turn off the height filter and zoom out, and you'll likely find it much easier to, for example, find your way through the frozen sameness of Everfrost paths. ;)
<p>With EQ having hit an all-time high of more than 118,000 simultaneous users recently, they've announced the launch of another new server, named Maelin Starpyre. For a limited time they will allow folks (for a fee) to movelog from other servers, complete with all their gear. Details can be found on <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/news_section/newsview.jsp?story=54511" target="_new">EQLive</a>.</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 27, 2003 - Spell Research</span>
<p>
With the launch of LoY, spell research combines began to be used for other tradeskill combines (tailoring). While I had always resisted tracking spell research on the site, due in part to various caster sites already containing the information, and in part from way too much on my plate already, I've decided to bend a little on this one. I will be tracking <a href="http://eqtraders.com/articles/article_page.php?article=g83&menustr=080105000000">new spell research combines</a> that came out with the LoY expansion, and only those combines. For those of you doing the happy-dance over this news, make sure to <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=4456">stop by the boards and thank Earenhylle Erlkoenig</a> for compiling a master-list of the new spell combines. ;)</font> </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 08:49:09&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 26, 2003 - Patch Update</span>
<p>
Some new bugs were fixed today, more are slated for the next patch. The bazaar bug that was giving folks an error message when they tried to buy stacks of items from player-vendors appears to be fixed. I believe the cast time on the charged spirit shift potion has also been fixed. Scheduled for the next patch is the fix to the collapsible bearskin potion bag and the collapsible medicine bag, which currently are only working for the new LoY alchemy. Also in the works for the next patch is the fix so that the 5-dose version of some of the LoY potions works properly 

We've made good progress on narrowing down trivials on the new recipes, and it's been a pretty productive week already. Now, if I could just beat my bank space into submission and magically juggle all the trade supplies onto 3 mules across the 2 accounts without having to character hop a gazillion times ... </p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 24, 2003 - Oh, Happy Day!!</span>
<p>
<table width="95%" border="0" cellpadding="5">
  <tr>
    <td><a href="http://www.gucomics.com"><img
      src="http://www.eqtraders.com/pics/gu_20030122.jpg" border="0" width="200"
      height="300"></a></td>
    <td>
      <p>While others might wax enthusiastic about frogloks as a playable race,
      new things to see, new mobs to kill, I suspect that the majority of
      tradeskillers are most excited about the doubling of their bank space. (I
      swear, even my mules have mules right now!) Of course, that's not to say
      that we're not eagerly awaiting the other bells and whistles that are in
      this new expansion, but the bank space thing tends to overshadow the rest.</p>
      <p>Once the servers are back up and folks have a chance to poke around,
      I'll update this spot with links to newly-found recipes.</p>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
