<p><span class="headers">February 17, 2003 - Less than a week to go!</span>
<p>
<p>That's right, folks, less than a week until the Legacy of Ykesha expansion goes live. As usual, you can expect things to be crazed around here once the day hits, as folks are scrambling all over the place finding new recipes, new drops, and cackling gleefully over the expanded bank space. I'll definitely be joining in the cackling for glee, in between gibbering as I try to do 30 different things at once. I'll try to get things up here on the main site, with links from the front page to the new recipes, as quickly as possible so that folks don't feel the need to hit the boards every 2 minutes for updates. ;)
<p>I'm also going to try to squeeze in some time, somehow this week, to get
another chunk of the ever-growing database ready before I have to stop to put
all my attention back into the boards and the main site for the flood of LoY
information. Yes, we're still working on the database; yes, it's going to be
very large and very comprehensive; no, we have no release date yet, but I hope
to have it into beta before I go to the Fan Faire at the end of March ... I
hope. {crosses fingers, toes and eyes}</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 07, 2003 - Evening Update</span>
<p>
<p>The trolls that were lugging along the cultural forge from Grobb to Neriak have
finally arrived at their destination, complied with local fire codes, and set up
the troll forge in Neriak's Foreign Quarter. Meanwhile, the frogs are settling
in nicely, and have industriously replaced all the stationary tradeskill
containers that were damaged during their claiming of Grobb with ones that are
more suited to their more diminutive statures.
<p>I suspect there will still be some changes to be seen, as both groups settle
into their new homes, but this will hopefully settle down some of the more ...
feisty ... tradeskillers a bit. ;) <i>(translation: Primal Scream has gotten a
bit overheated lately. Settle down in there and remember your manners! Just
because you're having a bad week and are upset is no need to ignore the "no
personal attacks" rule, and many of you seem to have forgotten that a) this
is "just a game", and b) there are real people with real feelings and
opinions behind those other personas. If you're THAT steamed about something,
take several steps back AND self-censor yourselves before we get fed up enough
to start doing more bannings, or temporarily close that forum until folks
remember common courtesy.)</i>
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 07, 2003 - Bad Froggies, Naughty Froggies!</span>
<p>
<p>It seems there is no end of troubles for the troll race right now. Not only have
they been kicked out of Grobb, and been forced to go bother the dark elves, but
along the way, they forgot to some very important items. (Trolls aren't known to
be the smartest of creatures, after all!) Among the things forgotten is their
cultural forge, which seems to have been uprooted from their old home, but which
hasn't yet shown up anywhere else. I expect it's going to take time for the dust
to settle, so, for now, things like the trade supplies listings for Grobb ... or
<a href="http://eqtraders.com/sources/source_zone_page.php?article=g89&menustr=110000000000&sz=1054">Gukta</a> ... or whatever
it's called today, are NOT going to be up-to-date. I'll make some temporary
pages as the weekend progresses, but I expect there will still be a lot of
changes incoming before things finally settle down.
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-06-13 08:50:31&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">February 06, 2003 - Another Patch</span>
<p>
<p>This is another day with a variety of things of interest to tradeskillers. As
usual, I'll add my commentary after each item:
<blockquote>
  <p>- Many Planar Recipes can now be used in collapsible containers. Some
  Planar Tailoring can only be done in the Tanaan Loom as opposed to the Planar
  Sewing Kit. Nothing that was previously made in the Loom was added to the
  collapsible tailoring kit. Skills changed were Baking, Sewing, Jewel Craft,
  and Fletching. <i>(Wheee! This is definitely a happy change for those packrats
  who have invested in collapsible containers. For those wondering, the only
  thing I can think of that specifically requires the PoK loom are parts for the
  planar armor quests</i><br>
  - Added gnome cultural recipe book to Ak'Anon. <i>(Using clockwork armor as a
  base, these are <a href="http://eqtraders.com/recipes/recipe_page.php?article=140&rsa=Tinkering&sub=armor&sb=item&menustr=080120040000">tinkered
  armors with some brewing and imbuing required</a>.)</i><br>
  - Changed the weights on Spiritstones to be more in line with Faithstones. <i>(Spiritstones
  were changed from weight 20.0 to weight 0.1 to match the weights on the cleric
  faithstones. Additionally, ogre and troll shammies, please note that the
  Spiritstone of Innothule is now Spiritstone of the Banished, and it ports you
  to Nektulos, not Innothule. We expect to see the storyline explanation for
  this change "soon")</i><br>
  - Changed Collapsible Jeweler's Kit to 6 slots from 4. <i>(The planar
  jeweller's kit has 6 slots, so this is just fixing it to match)</i><br>
  </p>
</blockquote>
<p>Additionally:</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>- Fixed a bug that caused merchants to charge a little extra or less (1
  copper).<i> (We've long known that vendors do creative rounding when you're
  buying multiples of items. I suspect that this might fix that.)</i><br>
  </p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'll likely have further updates to this later in the day, once I am more
caffeinated.
</p>
